{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75575b74-b262-4f3f-be5e-518d48b1f4c8","content":"No files found in the current directory. Here's how to do it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `x:DataType` attribute to the `ContentPage` root element, pointing to your ViewModel's full type:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat single `x:DataType` declaration is all that's needed — every `{Binding}` under it is now **compiled** and resolved against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, any typo (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure. To ensure this is enforced project-wide:\n\n**In your `.csproj`**, confirm these are present (they're on by default in .NET 7+ MAUI templates):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <MauiXamlCEnabled>true</MauiXamlCEnabled>    <!-- XAML compilation on -->\n    <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors> <!-- optional: promotes warnings -->\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key rules to remember\n\n| Scenario | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| Binding to a different type inside a `DataTemplate` | Add `x:DataType` on the template root element |\n| Need a runtime-only binding (e.g., `RelativeSource`) | Opt out with `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element |\n| Property doesn't exist on the declared type | **Build error** ✅ |\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, bindings are type-checked by the compiler — misspelled or missing properties will fail the build immediately.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"59055a6f-3e36-4221-b38b-5c5a53084dc7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. I'll provide guidance without needing to modify actual files.","outputTokens":646,"requestId":"3C37:3DCB6E:DA2B62:10DB900:6A0128BE"},"id":"ddb22b4d-0947-4d78-92e6-77cc0cc071e7","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:36.461Z","parentId":"9f2e7eb6-d541-4dee-b42f-be3023328168"}
